    <is_us_export>No</is_us_export>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Data regarding hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) recurrence after directly acting antivirals&#xD;
      (DAAs) given for hepatitis C virus treatment are contradictory. Surprisingly, some studies&#xD;
      reported that DAAs are accompanied with higher HCC recurrence. But, other studies showed no&#xD;
      rise or even decrease in HCC recurrence. Most of these studies were retrospective and some&#xD;
      were non-randomized prospective studies. Here investigators aim to perform a randomized&#xD;
      controlled trial to study this issue.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
